<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-62-0488 </DOCNO><TEXT>Legal problems of the erection and operation of industrial plants withregard to air pollution are discussed. Legal opinions are presented andsolutions are given which will facilitate practical dealing with thisfield of legislation on the basis of the following main subjects: Substantivelaw on licensing; licensing procedures, legal protection in the refusaland granting of licences; subsequent orders; refusal, shutdown, and decommissioningof plants; revocation of plant licences - articles 20, 21 of the FederalAct for the Protection Against Nuisances. This second edition incorporatesthe new aspects that have been brought in by the acceptance of the principleof precautionary action and measures, and by the landmark court decisionspassed in the field of atomic energy law, which can to a large extentbe applied to industrial plant subject to licensing according to theFederal Act for Protection Against Nuisances (BImSchG). (orig./HSCH).</TEXT></DOC>